    What does Luna mean?
    Moon
    The word lūna, which means Moon in Latin, is the origin of the given name Luna.

    यसमार्फत खोज्नुहोस्: What does Luna mean?
    What exactly is Luna?
    Luna commonly refers to: Earth's Moon, named "Luna" in Latin, Spanish and other languages. Luna (goddess), the ancient Roman personification of the Moon. Luna (name), including a list of people and characters with this given name and surname. Luna marble, the ancient Roman term for Carrara marble.

    यसमार्फत खोज्नुहोस्: What exactly is Luna?
    Is Luna is a Moon?
    Earth's only natural satellite is simply called "the Moon" because people didn't know other moons existed until Galileo Galilei discovered four moons orbiting Jupiter in 1610. In Latin, the Moon was called Luna, which is the main adjective for all things Moon-related: lunar.

    Moon Facts - NASA Science

    NASA Science
    https://science.nasa.gov › moon › facts
    NASA Science
    https://science.nasa.gov › moon › facts
    यसमार्फत खोज्नुहोस्: Is Luna is a Moon?
    What is a Luna female?
    In Sabine and ancient Roman religion and myth, Luna is the divine embodiment of the Moon (Latin Lūna [ˈɫ̪uːnä]). She is often presented as the female complement of the Sun, Sol, conceived of as a god.

    विवरण

    अङ्ग्रेजी भाषाबाट अनुवाद गरिएको-Amazon Luna एक क्लाउड गेमिङ प्लेटफर्म हो जुन Amazon द्वारा विकसित र संचालित छ। प्लेटफर्ममा ट्विचसँग एकीकरण छ र विन्डोज, म्याक, अमेजन फायर टिभी, आईओएस र एन्ड्रोइडमा उपलब्ध छ। Ubisoft+ र Jackbox Games जस्ता ब्रान्डका खेलहरू र च्यानलहरू Luna+ सशुल्क सदस्यता मार्फत पहुँच गरिन्छ। विकिपीडिया (अङ्ग्रेजी)
    मूल विवरण हेर्नुहोस्मूल विवरण हेर्नुहोस्

    विवरण

    Amazon Luna is a cloud gaming platform developed and operated by Amazon. The platform has integration with Twitch and is available on Windows, Mac, Amazon Fire TV, iOS as well as Android. Games and channels from brands such as Ubisoft+ and Jackbox Games are accessed via the Luna+ paid subscription.
